    • getIdTransactionPosWithPossibleTransactionByIdTransactionPos

      @Query(nativeQuery=true) Integer[][] getIdTransactionPosWithPossibleTransactionByIdTransactionPos(List<Integer> idTransactionPosList)
      Finds potential transaction matches for the specified import position IDs. Is used to indicate to the user that the item to be imported may already exist as a transcation.

      For each imp_trans_pos in idTransactionPosList where no transaction has yet been confirmed (ip.id_transaction IS NULL) but a match is flagged (ip.id_transaction_maybe invalid input: '<'> 0 OR ip.id_transaction_maybe IS NULL), this query:

      • Joins on transaction by matching security ID, transaction type, cash account, date, and units
      • Also requires either the cash-account amount to match (t.id_cash_account = ip.cashaccount_amount) or the recorded quotation to match (ip.quotation = t.quotation)
      Results are ordered by import position ID.
      Parameters:
      idTransactionPosList - list of import position IDs to evaluate
      Returns:
      a two-dimensional Integer array where each element is [id_trans_pos, id_transaction]

    • getIdTransactionPosWithPossibleTransactionByIdTransactionHead

      @Query(nativeQuery=true) Integer[][] getIdTransactionPosWithPossibleTransactionByIdTransactionHead(Integer idTransactionHead)
      Finds potential transaction matches for all import positions under the given header.

      Identical matching logic to the position-level lookup, scoped to ip.id_trans_head = ?1:

      • Filters for unconfirmed positions with a “maybe” flag
      • Joins on transaction by security ID, transaction type, cash account, date, and units
      • Requires either matching cash-account amount or matching quotation
      Distinct pairs are returned and ordered by import position ID.
      Parameters:
      idTransactionHead - import header ID whose positions to match
      Returns:
      a two-dimensional Integer array of [id_trans_pos, id_transaction]

    • findByIsinAndCurrencyWithNoSecurity

      @Query(nativeQuery=true) List<ImportTransactionPos> findByIsinAndCurrencyWithNoSecurity(String isin, String currency)
      Finds import transaction positions that match the given ISIN and currency but have no security assigned. Used to auto-assign securities after GTNet import successfully links or creates a security.

      Currency matching logic:

      • Matches against currency_security if present
      • Falls back to currency_account if currency_security is null
      Named query: ImportTransactionPos.findByIsinAndCurrencyWithNoSecurity
      Parameters:
      isin - the ISIN to match
      currency - the currency to match against
      Returns:
      list of import transaction positions without assigned security matching the ISIN and currency
